[68.321151, "o", "BUG FIX SUMMARY\r\n===============\r\n\r\nProblem:\r\n--------\r\nThe scheduler was sending meeting reminders at incorrect times (off by 1 hour)\r\nfor meetings between 2am-3am local time, specifically during DST transitions.\r\n\r\nRoot Cause:\r\n-----------\r\nIn app.py, the convert_to_berlin() function was using:\r\n  berlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)\r\n\r\nThis incorrectly treated the naive datetime (which represented UTC) as if it\r\nwere already in Berlin time, then just added timezone info.\r\n\r\nThe Fix:\r\n--------\r\nChanged to the correct two-step conversion:\r\n  utc_dt_aware = UTC_TZ.localize(utc_dt)      # Mark as UTC\r\n  berlin_dt = utc_dt_aware.astimezone(BERLIN_TZ)  # Convert to Berlin\r\n\r\nThis properly handles DST transitions.\r\n\r\nExample (Maintenance Window Prep meeting):\r\n------------------------------------------\r\nUTC Time: 2024-03-31 01:30:00\r\n\r\nOLD (buggy):  2024-03-31 01:30:00+01:00 CET  (Wrong!)\r\n"]
[68.3212, "o", "NEW (fixed):  2024-03-31 03:30:00+02:00 CEST (Correct!)\r\n\r\nOn March 31, 2024, Berlin springs forward to DST at 2am, so UTC+01:30\r\ncorrectly becomes Berlin 03:30 CEST (UTC+2).\r\n\r\nFiles Modified:\r\n--------------\r\n- /home/user/scheduler/app.py (fixed convert_to_berlin function)\r\n- Backup saved as app.py.backup\r\n\r\nThe crontab remains unchanged and will now work correctly.\r\n"]
